data.name: Aipom

attacks.name: Pilfer
attacks.text: Shuffle Aipom and all cards attached to it into your deck. Flip a coin. If heads, shuffle a card from your discard pile into your deck.

attacks.name: Tail Rap
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

data.flavorText: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

abilities.name: Snappy Move
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), if Aipom is on your Bench, you may draw a card. Then, discard all cards attached to Aipom and put Aipom on the bottom of your deck. You can't use more than 1 Snappy Move Poké-Power each turn.

attacks.name: Snap Tail
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 10 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

data.name: Aipom

attacks.name: Tail Code
attacks.text: Move an Energy card attached to the Defending Pokémon to another of your opponent's Pokémon.

attacks.name: Tail Smash
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

data.name: Aipom

attacks.name: Grab
attacks.text: Choose a Trainer card attached to 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. Your opponent shuffles that card into his or her deck.

data.flavorText: It lives atop tall trees. When leaping from branch to branch, it deftly uses its tail for balance.

data.name: Aipom

attacks.name: Collect
attacks.text: Draw a card.

attacks.name: Hand Trick
attacks.text: Return Aipom and all cards attached to it to your hand. (If you don't have any Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.)

data.flavorText: It lives atop giant trees. It wraps its tail around a branch so it won't fall off while asleep.

data.name: Aipom

attacks.name: Imitate
attacks.text: Draw cards until you have the same number of cards in your hand as your opponent.

data.flavorText: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

attacks.name: Last Resort
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

data.flavorText: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.

attacks.name: Throw Off
attacks.text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Pokémon. This attack does 20 damage to that Pokémon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.) Before doing damage, discard all Pokémon Tool cards attached to that Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It uses its tail to pluck fruits that are out of reach. Its tail is more adept than its real hands.

attacks.name: Fiddle Around
attacks.text: Look at the top 3 cards of your opponent's deck and put them back in any order.

data.flavorText: Its tail is so powerful that it can use it to grab a tree branch and hold itself up in the air.

attacks.name: Stretch Tail
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokémon and this attack does 10 damage to it. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokémon.)

attacks.name: Skedaddle
attacks.text: Return Aipom and all basic Energy cards attached to it to your hand. If you have no Benched Pokémon, this attack does nothing.

attacks.name: Double Hit
attacks.text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 10 damage times the number of heads.

data.flavorText: It lives high among the treetops. It can us its tail as freely and cleverly as its hands.

abilities.name: Scampering Tail
abilities.text: Once during your turn (before your attack), you may put the top card of your opponent's deck on the bottom of their deck without looking at it.

data.flavorText: As it did more and more with its tail, its hands became clumsy. It makes its nest high in the treetops.

attacks.name: Bustle
attacks.text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from and effects of attacks done to this Pokémon.

data.flavorText: It searches for prey from the tops of trees. When it spots its favorite food, Bounsweet, Aipom gets excited and pounces.

data.flavorText: This treetop dweller possesses a tail as dexterous as a hand. Ancient writings describe this Pokémon as a one-armed oddity.
